      • getFibonacci

        public static long getFibonacci(int n)
        Return the n^{th} Fibonacci number. The n^{th} Fibonacci number is defined as follows:
        Fib( 0 ) = 0
        Fib( 1 ) = 1
        Fib( n ) = Fib( n-1 ) + Fib( n-2 ) for n > 1
        Parameters:
        n -
        Returns:
        the n^{th} Fibonacci number
